  "commentary": "With SPX at 6783.75 sitting just above the 6775 flip line in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will mechanically sell into any rallies toward the massive 6800 wall (72.4B GEX) while buying dips toward 6765 support. The wall_break detection combined with the strong negative momentum (-6.7% 1-min, -7.8% 5-min) suggests dealers are actively buying this dip as hedging flows kick in below the flip. Key levels: defend 6775 flip and 6765 max negative gamma zone, with heavy resistance stacked from 6780-6800 creating a natural ceiling.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce attempt back toward 6785-6790 with dealers providing support on further weakness.",
